title: Omar Kelly grades the Dolphins' performance vs. Titans
text:
Omar Kelly grades the Dolphins' performance vs. Titans Caption PASSING GAME: B Jim Rassol / Sun Sentinel 
Quarterback Ryan Tannehill rebounded from two disastrous performances against the Bills and Jets to have an efficient game (97.8 passer rating) against a good Titans pass defense. Tannehill threw two touchdown passes to his tight ends, and both interceptions he threw weren’t his fault (one was off of a tip, and the other was a miscommunication with Jordan Cameron). Most importantly, Tannehill was aggressive with his throws (9.17 yards per attempt).

Most importantly, Tannehill was aggressive with his throws (9.17 yards per attempt). (Jim Rassol / Sun Sentinel) Caption RUNNING GAME: A Jim Rassol / Sun Sentinel 
The Dolphins pounded the Titans on the ground, gaining 124 of the team’s 180 rushing yards in the first half. Jarvis Landry’s 22-yard touchdown run was a work of art, and Lamar Miller (113 rushing yards and a touchdown on 19 carries) proved he’s still a dangerous NFL starter. The Dolphins’ offensive line -- especially new starting right guard Billy Turner -- deserves plenty of credit for opening up respectable holes.
